results.name: Product of iterated phi(n).
comment: A logarithmic plot of this sequence shows an unusual banded structure.
link: T. D. Noe, Table of n, a(n) for n=1..10000
T. D. Noe, Plot of A092694
example: a(100) = 40960 because the iterations of phi (40, 16, 8, 4, 2, 1) have a product of 40960.
mathematica: nMax=100; a=Table[1, {nMax}]; Do[e=EulerPhi[n]; a[[n]]=e*a[[e]], {n, 2, nMax}]; a
program: a092694 n = snd $ until ((== 1) . fst) f (a000010 n, 1) where
xref: Cf. A003434 (iterations of phi(n) needed to reach 1), A092693 (iterated phi sum).
